<text id="APB0194T">

<body>
<div1 type="summary">
<p>Lead shipments.</p>
</div1>

<div1 type="body">


<p><location_mentioned>Mine a Burton</location_mentioned> <date_mentioned n="06-04-1811">June 4</date_mentioned></p>
<p><person_mentioned>Mr James Bryan</person_mentioned></p>

<p><person_mentioned>Mr Ayres</person_mentioned> has on board his Waggon Barres lead in all
pounds. 750 of which is of your lead and 212 from my furnace which
I have given him to make out the load <person_mentioned>Mr Bates</person_mentioned> has this day Visited
<person_mentioned>Mr Westover</person_mentioned> to obtain an order for lead at <location_mentioned><person_mentioned>Mr Elliott</person_mentioned>s</location_mentioned>—<person_mentioned>P W Love</person_mentioned>
could not load the Cart—</p>

<p><person_mentioned>Moses Austin</person_mentioned>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>Reced from <person_mentioned>Moses Austin</person_mentioned> Nineteen-Barrs lead which I promes</p>

<p>to—delivere <person_mentioned>Mr Bryan</person_mentioned> <location_mentioned>Saint Genevieve</location_mentioned> with out, delay—As Witness
my hand—this <date_mentioned n="06-04-1811">4 day <hi rend="italic">June 1811</hi></date_mentioned></p>

<p><person_mentioned>Francis (his x mark) Ayres</person_mentioned></p>
<p>Attest   <person_mentioned>G. W. <hi rend="italic">Treat</hi></person_mentioned></p>

</div1>
